t effect.\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a duetof La Vie\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5070}, {\"ngram\": \"Rose\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5078}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 5084, \"to\": 5091}, {\"ngram\": \"that effect\", \"from\": 5104, \"to\": 5115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After her rendition, she said it was her 'supreme honour' to perform at the event.\", \"from\": 5118, \"to\": 5200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her rendition\", \"from\": 5124, \"to\": 5137}, {\"ngram\": \"her 'supreme honour\", \"from\": 5155, \"to\": 5174}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5190, \"to\": 5199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stiff-person syndrome (SPS) is a rare autoimmune movement disorder that affects the central nervous system (the brain and spinal cord).\", \"from\": 5202, \"to\": 5337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5207, \"end\": 5228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stiff-person_syndrome\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stiff-person syndrome\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stiff-person_syndrome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stiff-person_syndrome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rare autoimmune movement disorder\", \"from\": 5233, \"to\": 5268}, {\"ngram\": \"the central nervous system\", \"from\": 5282, \"to\": 5308}, {\"ngram\": \"the brain\", \"from\": 5310, \"to\": 5319}, {\"ngram\": \"spinal cord\", \"from\": 5324, \"to\": 5335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SPS is characterised by fluctuating muscle rigidity in the trunk and limbs and a heightened sensitivity to stimuli such as noise, touch, and emotional distress, which can set off muscle spasms.\", \"from\": 5339, \"to\": 5532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5329, \"end\": 5340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spinal_cord\", \"score\": 0.9966181535644918, \"rank\": 0.003393322130290925, \"text\": \"spinal cord\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spinal_cord\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spinal_cord\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"muscle rigidity\", \"from\": 5375, \"to\": 5390}, {\"ngram\": \"the trunk\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5403}, {\"ngram\": \"limbs\", \"from\": 5408, \"to\": 5413}, {\"ngram\": \"a heightened sensitivity\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5442}, {\"ngram\": \"stimuli\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5453}, {\"ngram\": \"noise\", \"from\": 5462, \"to\": 5467}, {\"ngram\": \"touch\", \"from\": 5469, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"emotional distress\", \"from\": 5480, \"to\": 5498}, {\"ngram\": \"muscle spasms\", \"from\": 5518, \"to\": 5531}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stiff-person syndrome is extremely rare.\", \"from\": 5533, \"to\": 5573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5523, \"end\": 5536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spasticity\", \"score\": 0.7546610953705667, \"rank\": 0.32509812170595886, \"text\": \"muscle spasms\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spasticity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spasticity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only about one out of every one million people have been diagnosed with this syndrome.\", \"from\": 5575, \"to\": 5661, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every one million people\", \"from\": 5597, \"to\": 5621}, {\"ngram\": \"this syndrome\", \"from\": 5647, \"to\": 5660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twice as many women have stiff person syndrome as men.\", \"from\": 5662, \"to\": 5716, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"as many women\", \"from\": 5668, \"to\": 5681}, {\"ngram\": \"stiff person syndrome\", \"from\": 5687, \"to\": 5708}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 5712, \"to\": 5715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Symptoms can occur at any age but usually develop between ages 30 and 60.\", \"from\": 5717, \"to\": 5790, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Symptoms\", \"from\": 5717, \"to\": 5725}, {\"ngram\": \"any age\", \"from\": 5739, \"to\": 5